.TH "memblock_phys_alloc_range" 9 "memblock_phys_alloc_range" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
memblock_phys_alloc_range \- allocate a memory block inside specified range
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "phys_addr_t" memblock_phys_alloc_range
.BI "(phys_addr_t size "  ","
.BI "phys_addr_t align "  ","
.BI "phys_addr_t start "  ","
.BI "phys_addr_t end "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "size" 12
size of memory block to be allocated in bytes
.IP "align" 12
alignment of the region and block's size
.IP "start" 12
the lower bound of the memory region to allocate (physical address)
.IP "end" 12
the upper bound of the memory region to allocate (physical address)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate \fIsize\fP bytes in the between \fIstart\fP and \fIend\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
physical address of the allocated memory block on success,
0 on failure.
